I have a Blazor wasm chat app where i want a `textarea` element to submit the `form` on pressing the `enter` key but prevent the default behaviour of the element which is appending a new line.

Now, using the `@onkeydown` and `@onkeyup` i was able to isolate this behaviour where now the `textarea` element submits the form on enter but also appends a new line with `shift`+`enter` and it's working fine.

Sample code:
```
<textarea rows="1" 
                                  @bind-value="@MessageModel.Message" 
                                  @bind-value:event="oninput" 
                                  @onkeydown="MessageOnDown" 
                                  @onkeyup="MessageOnUp" 
                                  id="MessageTextArea"
                                  placeholder="Type a message..."></textarea>
@code {
        readonly Dictionary<string, string> Keys = new Dictionary<string, string>();

        private async Task MessageOnDown(KeyboardEventArgs keyboardEventArgs)
        {
            Keys[keyboardEventArgs.Key] = keyboardEventArgs.Key;

            if (keyboardEventArgs.Key == "Enter" && Keys.Count == 1)
            {
                if (editContext.Validate())
                {
                    await ValidSubmit();
                }
            }
        }

        private void MessageOnUp(KeyboardEventArgs keyboardEventArgs)
        {
            Keys.Remove(keyboardEventArgs.Key);
        }

        private async Task ValidSubmit()
        {
            //Send message logic...
        }
}
```
But there is a small caveat where just before submitting the form (on pressing the enter key) a new line is appended.
Now, instead of using `@onkeydown:preventDefault` which blocks pressing any key in the textarea. 

My question is:
Can we have the option to call `PreventDefault` inside the EventHandler at a certain step during execution like we do in javascript? So for example we can call prevent default on a condition where a specific key is pressed like the `enter` key in my example. 

So the desired behaviour would be something like this:

```
private async Task MessageOnDown(KeyboardEventArgs keyboardEventArgs)
        {
            Keys[keyboardEventArgs.Key] = keyboardEventArgs.Key;

            if (keyboardEventArgs.Key == "Enter" && Keys.Count == 1)
            {
                keyboardEventArgs.PreventDefault();
                if (editContext.Validate())
                {
                    await ValidSubmit();
                }
            }
        }
```

To be honest i don't know if this is possible to achieve in Blazor so i completely understand if it's not.

The app is available here [Zen-Chat](https://github.com/hmz777/Zen-Chat).
And here is the component which the example code above is from [ChatSection.razor.cs](https://github.com/hmz777/Zen-Chat/blob/master/Client/Shared/ChatSection.razor.cs).

Thank you.

